  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Understanding and Addressing Conflict Drivers and Migration Routes in Agadez</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to help to resolve the destabilizing effects that can be associated with migration movements through Agadez (Niger) and recent changes in migration management policies in the Agadez region, and builds the capacity of local civil society to address tensions between migrants and the host community. The project also creates alternative economic opportunities for aggrieved host community members who are struggling due to the downturn in the migration-based economy in the region. While the project works to create innovative and sustainable economic opportunities for the most vulnerable members of the host community, some of these activities include providing migrants with day jobs to create not only a platform for exchange between migrants and members of the host community, but also to offer migrants a chance to earn money which can then be reinvested in the communities.</narrative>
  </description>
